keywords:
  - mouse gait
  - paw print
  - gait analysis
  - R Shiny
  - neuroscience
  - walking assay
abstract: >
  GaitTrackR is an interactive R Shiny application for analyzing mouse gait
  from paw-print coordinate data. Starting from individual paw positions,
  it computes mouse-level gait metrics (step length, front-hind distance,
  perpendicular deviation) and visualizes them across genotypes and treatments
  using descriptive statistics.
